obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (71045)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Tenants having right of occupancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71045&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant-`
  line
  line `(a) who at the commencement of this Act has for more than two generations in the male line of`
  line `descent through a grandfather or grand-uncle and for a period of not less than twenty years been`
  line `occupying land paying no rent thereof beyond the amount of the land-revenue thereof and the rates`
  line `and cesses for the time being chargeable thereon, or`
  line
  line `(b) who having owned land, and having ceased to be landowner thereof otherwise than by`
  line `forfeiture to the Government or than by any voluntary act, has, since he ceased to be landowner,`
  line `continuously occupied the land, or`
  line
  line `(c) who, in a village or estate in which he settled along with, or was settled by, the founder thereof`
  line `as a cultivator therein, occupied land on the twenty-first day of October, 1868, and has continuously`
  line `occupied the land since that date, or`
  line
  line `(d) who, being jagirdar of the estate or any part of the estate in which the land occupied by him is`
  line `situate, has continuously occupied the land for not less than twenty years, or , having been such`
  line `jagirdar, occupied the land while he was jagirdar and has continuously occupied it for not less than`
  line `twenty years,`
  line
  line `Has a right of occupancy in the land so occupied, unless, in the case of a tenant belonging to the`
  line `class specified in clause (c), the landlord proves that the tenant was settled on land previously cleared`
  line `and brought under cultivation by, or at the expense of, the founder.`
  line
  line `(2) If a tenant proves that he has continuously occupied land for thirty years and paid no rent there for`
  line `beyond the amount of the land-revenue thereof and the rates and cesses for the time being chargeable`
  line `thereon, it may be presumed that he has fulfilled the conditions of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) the words in that clause denoting natural relationship denote also relationship by adoption,`
  line `including therein the customary appointment of an heir, and relationship by the usage of a religious`
  line community.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (71269)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Right of occupancy of other tenants recorded as having the right before passing of Punjab Tenancy Act, 1868.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71269&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A tenant recorded in a record-of-rights sanctioned by the Local Government before`
  line `the twenty first day of October, 1868, as a tenant having a right of occupancy in land which he has`
  line `continuously occupied from the time of the preparation of that record, shall be deemed to have a right of`
  line `occupancy in that land unless the contrary has been established by a decree of a competent Court in a suit`
  line `instituted before the passing of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (71047)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Right of occupancy in land taken in exchange.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71047&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If the tenant has voluntarily exchanged the land,`
  line `or any portion of the land, formerly occupied by him for other land belonging to the same landlord, the`
  line `land taken in exchange shall be held to be subject to the same right of occupancy as that to which the land`
  line `given in exchange would have been subject if the exchange had not taken place.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (71048)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Establishment of right of occupancy on grounds other than those expressly stated in Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71048&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing sections of this Chapter shall preclude any person from establishing a`
  line `right of occupancy on any ground other than the grounds specified in those sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (71049)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Right of occupancy not to be acquired by mere lapse of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71049&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No tenant shall acquire a right of`
  line `occupancy by mere lapse of time.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (71050)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Right of occupancy not to be acquired by joint owner in land held in joint ownership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71050&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line In
  line `the absence of a custom to the contrary no one of several joint owners of land shall acquire a right of`
  line `occupancy under this Chapter in land jointly owned by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (71051)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Continuance of existing occupancy rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71051&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing sections`
  line `of this Chapter, a tenant who immediately before the commencement of this Act has a right of occupancy`
  line `in any land under an enactment specified in any line of the first column of the following table shall, when`
  line `this Act comes into force, be held to have, for all the purposes of this Act, a right of occupancy in that`
  line `land under the enactment specified in the same line of the second column of the table :—`
  line `PUNJAB TENANCY ACT, 1868 THIS ACT.`
  line
  line `(XXVIII 1868)`
  line
  line `FIRST COLUMN SECOND COLUMN`
  line
  line `Section. Clause. Section. Sub-Section. Clause.`
  line
  line `5 (1) 5 (1) (a)`
  line
  line `5 (2) 5 (1) (b)`
  line
  line `5 (3) 5 (1) (c)`
  line
  line `5 (4) 5 (1) (d)`
  line
  line `6 ... 6 ... ...`
  line
  line `8 ... 8 ... ...`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (71052)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Respective rights of landlord and tenant to produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71052&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rent for the time being payable`
  line `in respect of a tenancy shall be the first charge on the produce thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A tenant shall be entitled to tend, cut and harvest the produce of his tenancy in due course of`
  line `husbandry without any interference on the part of his landlord.`
  line
  line `(3) Except where rent is taken by division of the produce, the tenant shall be entitled to the exclusive`
  line `possession of the produce.`
  line
  line `(4) Where rent is taken by division of the produce.—`
  line
  line `(a) the tenanat shall be entitled to the exclusive possession of the whole produce until it is divided:`
  line
  line `(b) the landlord shall be entitled to be present at, and take part in, the division of the produce; and`
  line
  line `(c) when the produce has been divided, the landlord shall be entitled to the possession or his share`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (71053)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Commutation and alteration of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71053&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where rent is taken by any of the following methods,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) by division or appraisement of the produce,`
  line
  line `(b) by rates fixed with reference to the nature of the crops grown,`
  line
  line `(c) by a rate on a recognized measure of area,`
  line
  line `(d) by a rent in gross on the tenency, or`
  line
  line `(e) partly by one of the methods specified in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of this sub-section and partly`
  line `by another or others of them,`
  line `One of those methods shall not be commuted in whole or in part into another without the consent of`
  line `both landlord and tenant.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of a contract or a decree or order of competent authority to the contrary, a tenant`
  line `whose rent is taken by any of the methods specified in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1), or by the`
  line `method specified in clause (d) of that sub-section, shall not be liable to pay for a tenancy rent at any`
  line `higher rate, or of a higher amount, as the case may be, than the rate or amount payable in respect of the`
  line `tenancy for the preceding agricultural year.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (71054)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Payments for land occupied without consent of landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71054&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any person in possession of land`
  line `occupied without the consent of the landlord shall be liable to pay for the use or occupation of that land at`
  line `the rate of rent payable in the preceding agricultural year, or, if rent was not payable in that year, at such`
  line `rate as the Court may determine to be fair and equitable.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (71055)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Collection of rents of undivided property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71055&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When two or more persons are landlord of a tenant`
  line `in respect of the same tenancy, the tenant shall not be bound to pay part of the rent of his tenancy to one`
  line `of those persons and part to another`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (71056)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Presumption with respect to produce removed before division or appraisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71056&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where rent`
  line `is taken by division or appraisement of the produce, if the tenant removes any portion of the produce at`
  line `such a time or in such a manner as to prevent the due division or appraisement thereof ,or deals therewith`
  line `in a manners contrary to established usage the produce may be deemed to have been as full as the fullest`
  line `crop of the same description on similar lands in the neighborhood for that harvest.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (71057)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment of referee for division or appraisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71057&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If either the landlord or the tenant`
  line `neglects to attend, either personally or by agent, at the proper time for making the division or`
  line `appraisement of the produce, or if there is a dispute about the division or appraisement, a Revenue-officer`
  line `may, on the application of either party, appoint such person as he thinks fit to be a referee to divide or`
  line `appraise the produce.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (71058)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appointment of assessors and procedure of referee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71058&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Revenue-officer appoints`
  line `referee under the last forgoing section, he may, in his discretion, give him instructions with respect to the`
  line `association with himself of any other persons as assessors, the number, qualification and selection of`
  line `those assessor, and the procedure to be followed in making`
  line `the division or appraisement.`
  line
  line `(2) The referee so appointed shall make the division or appraisement in accordance with any`
  line `instructions which he may have received from the Revenue-officer under the last foregoing`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `(3) Before making the division or appraisement the referee shall give notice to the landlord and the`
  line `tenant of the time and place at which the division or appraisement will be made, but, of either the landlord`
  line `or the tenant fails to attend either personally or by agent, the referee`
  line `may proceed exparte.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of making the division or appraisement, the referee, with his assessors, if any, may`
  line `enter upon any land on which or into any building in which the produce is.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (71059)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Procedure after division or appraisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71059&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The result of the division or appraisement shall`
  line `be recorded and signed by the referee, and the record shall be submitted to the Revenue-officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue-officer shall consider the record, and, after such further inquiry, if any, as he may`
  line `deem necessary, shall make an order either confirming or varying the`
  line `division or appraisement.`
  line
  line `(3) The Revenue-officer shall also make such order as to the costs of the reference as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The costs may include the remuneration of the referee and of the assessors, if any, and may be`
  line `levied from the applicant before the appointment of the referee subject to adjustment at the close of the`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (71060)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Enhancement of produce - rents of occupancy tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71060&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where the rent of a tenant having a`
  line `right of occupancy in any land is a share of the produce, or of the appraised value thereof, with or without`
  line `an addition in money, or is paid according to rates fixed with reference to the nature of the crops grown,`
  line `or is a rent in gross payable in kind, the tenant shall be entitled to occupy`
  line `the land at that rent :`
  line
  line `Provided that, when the land or any part thereof previously not irrigated or flooded becomes irrigated`
  line `or flooded, the rent payable in respect of the land or part may, subject to the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `enhanced to the share or rates, or with reference to the rent in gross, as the case may be, paid by tenants,`
  line `having a similar right of occupancy, for irrigated or flooded land of a similar description and with similar`
  line advantages.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (71061)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Reduction of rents referred to in the last foregoing section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71061&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `When the land, or any part of the`
  line `land, held by a tenant having a right of occupancy to whom the last foregoing section applies ceases to be`
  line `irrigated or flooded, the rent payable in respect of the land or part may be reduced to the share or rates, or`
  line `with reference to the rent in gross, as the case may be, paid by tenants, having a similar right of`
  line `occupancy for unirrigated or unflooded land of a similar description and with similar advantages.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (71062)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Enhancement of cash rents of occupancy tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71062&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a tenant having a right of`
  line `occupancy pays his rent entirely by a cash-rate on a recognized measure of area or by a cash-rent in`
  line `gross on his tenancy, the rent may be enhanced on the ground that, after deduction therefrom of the`
  line `land revenue of, and the rates and cesses chargeable on, the tenancy, it is—`
  line
  line `(a) if the tenant belongs to the class specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 5, less`
  line `than two annas per rupee of the amount of the land-revenue;`
  line
  line `(b) if he belongs to any of the classes specified in clauses (b) , (c) and (d) of that sub-section`
  line `less than six annas per rupee of the amount of the land-revenue ;`
  line
  line `(c) if he belongs to the class specified in section 6, or if his right of occupancy is established`
  line `under section 8 and his rent is not regulated by contract, less than twelve annas per rupee of the`
  line `amount of the land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) In a case to which sub-section (1) applies, the rent may be enhanced to an amount not`
  line `exceeding two, six or twelve annas per rupee of the amount of the land-revenue as the case may be,`
  line `in addition to the amount of the land-revenue of the tenancy and the rates and cessers chargeable`
  line thereon.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (71063)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Reduction of rent referred to in the last foregoing section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71063&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The rent payable buy a tenant`
  line `to whom the last foregoing section applies may be reduced on the ground that the productive powers`
  line `of his tenancy have been decreased by a cause beyond his control.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (71065)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Enhancement and reduction of rent by suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71065&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue Court, on the suit of either`
  line `landlord or tenant, may, subject to the provisions of this and other sections of this Act, enhance or reduce`
  line `the rent of any tenant having a right of occupancy.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a decree for the enhancement of the rent of such a tenant has been passed under the Punjab`
  line `Tenancy Act, 1868, (XXVIII of 1868) a suit for a further enhancement of his rent shall not lie till the`
  line `expiration of five years from the date of the decree, unless in the meantime the local area in which the`
  line `land comprised in the decree is situate has been generally reassessed and the revenue payable in respect of`
  line `that land has been increased.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), a suit instituted for the enhancement of the rent of a`
  line `tenant having a right of occupancy shall not be entertained in either of the following cases, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) if within the ten years next preceding its institution his rent has been commuted under`
  line `section 13 or enhanced under this section,`
  line
  line `(b) if within that period a decree has been passed under this Act dismissing on the merits a suit for`
  line `the enhancement of his rent, unless the land or some part of the land comprised in his tenancy, not`
  line `having been irrigated or flooded at the time of such commutation, enhancement or decree, has become`
  line `irrigated or flooded.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (71066)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Discretion as to extent of enhancement or reduction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71066&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In enhancing or reducing the rent of any`
  line `land under the foregoing provisions of this chapter, the Court shall within the limits prescribed by those`
  line `provisions, enhance or reduce the rent to such an amount as it considers fair and equitable, but shall not in`
  line `any case fix the rent at a sum less than the amount of the land-revenue of the land and the rates and cesses`
  line `chargeable thereon`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (71067)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Time for enhancement or reduction to take effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71067&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `When a Revenue-officer of any class`
  line `who has been invested under the foregoing provisions of this Act with any powers to be exercised in any`
  line `local area is transferred from that local area to another as a Revenue-officer of the same or a higher class,`
  line `he shall continue to exercise those powers in that other local area unless the Local Government otherwise`
  line `directs or has otherwise directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (71068)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Adjustment of rents expressed in terms of the land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71068&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the rent of a tenancy`
  line `is the whole or a share of the land-revenue thereof, with or without an addition in money, kind or service,`
  line `and the land-revenue of the holding in which the tenancy is situate is altered, a Revenue-officer having`
  line `authority under section 56 of the Punjab Land-revenue Act, 1887 (XVII of 1887), to determine the`
  line `land-revenue payable in respect of the several holdings comprised in the estate in which the tenancy is`
  line `situate shall determine also the amount of the land-revenue of the tenancy, or the proportionate share`
  line `thereof, payable by the tenant as rent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an addition referred to in sub-section (1) is a percentage fixed with reference to the`
  line `land-revenue of the tenancy, or the whole or a share of the rates and cesses chargeable thereon, or both,`
  line `the Revenue-officer shall in like manner from time to time alter the amount of the addition in proportion`
  line `to any alteration of such land-revenue or rates and cesses.`
  line
  line `(3) The sum or sums determined under the foregoing sub-sections, together with any addition`
  line `previously payable other than the additions referred to in sub-section (2), shall be the rent payable in`
  line `respect of the tenancy until there is again an alterations of the land-revenue thereof or of the rates and`
  line `cesses chargeable thereon or until the rent is enhanced by a suit under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) An alteration of rent under this section shall not be deemed an enhancement or reduction of rent`
  line `within the meaning of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (71069)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Alteration of rent on alteration of area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71069&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every tenant shall-`
  line
  line `(a) be liable to pay additional rent for all land proved to be in excess of the area for which rent has`
  line `been preciously paid by him, unless it is proved that the excess is due to the addition to his tenancy of`
  line `land which, having previously belonged to the tenancy, was lost by alluvion or otherwise without any`
  line `reduction of the rent being made; and`
  line
  line `(b) be entitled to and abatement of rent in respect of any deficiency proved to exist in the area of`
  line `his tenancy as compared with the area for which rent has been previously paid by him, unless it is`
  line `proved that the deficiency is due to the loss of land which was added to the area of the tenancy by`
  line `alluvion or otherwise, and that an addition has not been made to the rent in respect of the addition to`
  line `the area.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining the area for which rent has been previously paid, the Court shall have regard to the`
  line `following, among other matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the origin and conditions of the tenant’s occupancy, for instance whether the rent was a rent in`
  line `gross for the entire tenancy;`
  line
  line `(b) whether the tenant has been allowed to hold additional land in consideration of and addition to`
  line `his total rent or otherwise with the knowledge and consent of the landlord; and`
  line
  line `(c) the length of time during which there has been no dispute as to rent or area.`
  line
  line `(3) In adding to or abating rent under this section, the Court shall add to or abate the rent to such an`
  line `amount as it deems to be fair and equitable, and shall specify in its decree the date on and from which the`
  line `addition or abatement is to take effect.`
  line
  line `(4) An addition to or abatement of rent under this section shall not be deemed an enhancement or`
  line `reduction of rent within the meaning of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (71070)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Remission of rent by Courts decreeing arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71070&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing`
  line `sections of this Chapter, if it appears to a Court making a decree for and arrear of rent that the area of a`
  line `tenancy has been so diminished by diluvion or otherwise, or that the produce thereof has been so`
  line `diminished by drought, hail, deposit of sand or other like calamity, that the full amount of rent payable by`
  line `the tenant cannot be equitably decreed, the Court may, with the previous sanction of the Collector, allow`
  line `such remission from the rent payable by the tenant as may appear to it to be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (71071)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Remission and suspension of rent consequent on like treatment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71071&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Wherever from any cause the payment of the whole or any part of the land-revenue`
  line `payable in respect of any land is remitted or suspended, a Revenue-officer may, by order, remit or`
  line `suspend, as the case may be, the payment of the rent of that land to an amount which may bear the same`
  line `proportion to the whole of the rent payable in respect of the land as the land-revenue of which the`
  line `payment has been remitted or suspended bears to the whole of the land-revenue in respect of the land.`
  line
  line `(2) An order passed under sub-section (1) shall not be liable to be contested by suit in any Court.`
  line
  line `(3) A suit shall not lie for the recovery of any rent of which the payment has been remitted, or, during`
  line `the period of suspension, of any rent of which the payment has been suspended.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the payment of rent has been suspended, the period during which the suspension has`
  line `continued shall be excluded in the computation of the period of limitation prescribed for a suit for the`
  line `recovery of the rent.`
  line
  line `(5) If the landlord collects any rent of which the payment has been remitted, or before the expiration of`
  line `the period of suspension collects any rent of which the payment has been suspended, the whole of the`
  line `land-revenue remitted or suspended in his favour shall become immediately payable by him.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section relating to the remission and suspension of the payment of rent may`
  line `be applied, so far as they can be made applicable, to land if which the land-revenue has been released,`
  line `compounded for or redeemed, in any case in which, if the land-revenue in respect of the land had not been`
  line `released, compounded for or redeemed, the whole or any part of it might, in the opinion or the Revenueofficer, be remitted or suspended under the rules for the time being in force for regulating the remission`
  line `and suspension of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (71072)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to deposit rent in certain cases with Revenue officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71072&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `In either of the following cases,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) when a landlord refuses to receive, or grant a receipt for, any rent payable in money when`
  line `tendered to him by a tenant,`
  line
  line `(b) when a tenant is in doubt as to the person entitled to receive rent payable in money, the tenant`
  line `may apply to a Revenue-officer for leave to deposit the rent in his office, and the Revenue-officer shall`
  line `receive the deposit if, after examining the applicant, he is satisfied that there is sufficient ground for`
  line `the application and if the applicant pays the fee, if any, chargeable for the issue of the notice next`
  line `hereinafter referred to.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (71073)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Effect of depositing rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71073&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a deposit has been so received, it shall be deemed to be a`
  line `payment made by the tenant to his landlord in respect of rent due.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue-officer receiving the deposit shall give notice of the receipt thereof to every person`
  line `who he has reason to believe claims or is entitled to the deposit, and may pay the amount thereof to any`
  line `person appearing to him to be entitled thereto, or may, if he thinks fit, retain the deposit pending the`
  line `decision of a competent Court as to the person so entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or other proceeding shall be instituted against the Secretary of State of India in Council, or`
  line `against any officer of the Government, in respect of anything done by a Revenue-officer under this`
  line `section, but noting in this sub-section shall prevent any person entitled to receive the amount of any such`
  line `deposit from recovering it from a person to whom it has been paid by a Revenue-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (71074)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Recovery of rent from attached produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71074&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an order is made by any Court for the`
  line `attachment of the produce of a tenancy or of any part of a tenancy, the landlord may apply to the`
  line `Revenue-officer by whom the attachment is to be or has been made to sell the produce and pay to him out`
  line `of the proceeds of the sale thereof the amount or value of —`
  line
  line `(a) any rent which has fallen due to him in respect of the tenancy within the year immediately`
  line `preceding the application and`
  line
  line `(b) the rent which will be falling due after the harvesting of the produce and is chargeable`
  line `against it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue-officer shall give the person at whose instance the attachment was made an`
  line `opportunity of showing cause why the application of the landlord should not be granted, and, if he finds`
  line `the landlord’s claim to the whole or any part of the rent to be proved, he shall cause the produce or such`
  line `portion thereof as he may deem necessary to be sold, and shall apply the proceeds of the sale in the first`
  line `instance to satisfy the claim.`
  line
  line `(3) The finding of the Revenue-officer under sub-section (2) shall have the force of a decree in a suit`
  line `between the landlord and the tenant`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (71075)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Treatment of leases for period exceeding or equal to term of assessment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71075&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a lease has been granted, or an agreement has been entered into, by a landowner in respect of`
  line `any land assessed to land-revenue, fixing for a period exceeding the term for which the land-revenue has been`
  line `assessed the rent or other sum payable in respect of the land under the lease or agreement, and that term has`
  line `expired, the lease or agreement shall be voidable—`
  line
  line `(a) at the option of the landowner if the land-revenue of the land has been enhanced and the person to`
  line `whom the lease has been granted or with whom the agreement has been entered into refuses to pay such`
  line `rent or other sum as a Revenue Court, on the suit of the landowner, determines to be fair and equitable;`
  line and
  line `where the relation of landlord and tenant exists between the grantor and grantee of the lease or between`
  line `the persons who entered into the agreement—`
  line
  line `(b) at the option of the tenant if the land-revenue of the land has been reduced and the landlord refuses`
  line `to accept such rent as a Revenue Court, on the suit of the tenant, determines to be fair and equitable.`
  line
  line `(2) Any agreement relative to the occupation, rent, profits or produce of any land which has been entered`
  line `into for the term of the currency of an assessment shall, unless a contrary intention clearly appears in the`
  line `agreement or the agreement is terminated by consent of parties or course of law, continue in force until a`
  line `revised assessment takes effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (71076)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Relinquishment by tenant for a fixed term.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71076&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `A tenant holding for a fixed term under a contract`
  line `or a decree or order of competent authority may relinquish his tenancy without notice at the end of that`
  line term.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (71077)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Relinquishment by any other tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71077&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any other tenant may relinquish his tenancy by`
  line `giving verbally or in writing to his landlord, or to his landlord’s agent, on or before the fifteenth day of`
  line `January in any year, notice of his intention to relinquish the tenancy at the end of the agricultural year`
  line `then current.`
  line
  line `(2) The tenant may, instead of, or in addition to giving the notice in the manner mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1), apply to a Revenue-officer on or before the date aforesaid to cause the notice to be served`
  line `on the landlord, and the Revenue-officer, on receiving the cost of service from the tenant, shall cause the`
  line `notice to be served as soon as may be.`
  line
  line `(3) If the tenant does not give notice in the manner prescribed in this section, he shall be liable to pay`
  line `the rent of his tenancy for any part of the ensuing agricultural year during which the tenancy is not let by`
  line `the landlord to some other person or is not cultivated by the landlord himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (71078)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Relinquishment of part only of a tenancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71078&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `A tenant cannot, without the consent of his landlord,`
  line `relinquish a part only of his tenancy`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (71079)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Abandonment of tenancy by occupancy tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71079&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `If a tenant having a right of occupancy fails`
  line `for more than one year without sufficient cause to cultivate his tenancy, either by himself or some other`
  line `person, and to arrange for payment of the rent thereof as it falls due, the right of occupancy shall be`
  line `extinguished from the end of that year.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (71089)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Time for ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71089&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `A decree or order for the ejectment of a tenant shall not be executed at any`
  line `other time than between the first day of May and the fifteenth day of June (both days inclusive), unless`
  line `the Court making the decree or, where the order is made under section 44, the officer making the order`
  line `otherwise directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (71090)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Relief against forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71090&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in a suit for the ejectment of a tenant on either of the grounds`
  line `mentioned in clauses (a) and (b) of section 39 or of section 40 it appears to the Court that the injury`
  line `caused by the act or omission on which the suit is based is capable of being remedied, or that an award of`
  line `compensation will be sufficient satisfaction to the landlord therefore, the Court may, instead of making a`
  line `decree for the ejectment of the tenant, order him to remedy the injury within a period to be fixed in the`
  line `order, or order him to pay into Court, within such a period, such compensation as the Court thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may from time to time, for special reasons, extend a period fixed by it under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If within the period, or extended period, as the case may be, fixed by the Court under this section,`
  line `the injury is remedied or the compensation is paid, a decree for the ejectment of the tenant shall not be`
  line made.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (71091)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Rights of ejected tenants in respect of crops and land prepared for sowing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71091&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where at the`
  line `time of the proposed ejectment of a tenant from any land his uncut or ungathered crops are standing on`
  line `any part thereof, he shall not be ejected from that part until the crops have ripened and he has been`
  line `allowed a reasonable time to harvest them.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court or Revenue-officer decreeing or ordering the ejectment of the tenant may, on the`
  line `application of the landlord, determine any dispute arising in consequence`
  line `of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) between the landlord and the tenant or between the landlord and any person entitled to`
  line `harvest discretion—`
  line
  line `(a) direct that the tenant pay for the longer occupation of the land secured to him under`
  line `sub-section (1) such rent as may be fair and equitable, or`
  line
  line `(b) determine the value of the tenant’s uncut and ungathered crops, and, on payment thereof by the`
  line `landlord to the Court or Revenue-officer, forthwith eject the tenant.`
  line
  line `(3) When a tenant for whose ejectment proceedings have been taken has, comfortably with local`
  line `usage, prepared for sowing any land comprised in his tenancy, but has not sown or planted crops on that`
  line `land, he shall be entitled to receive from the landlord before ejectment a fair equivalent in money for the`
  line `labour and capital expended by him in so preparing the land, and the Court or Revenue-officer before`
  line `which or whom proceedings, are pending shall, on the application of the tenant, determine the sum`
  line `payable to the tenant under this sub-section and stay his ejectment until that sum has been paid to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (71092)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Relief of wrongful dispossession or ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71092&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `In either of the following cases, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) if a tenant has been dispossessed without his consent of his tenancy or any part thereof`
  line `otherwise than in execution of a decree or than in pursuance of an order under section 44 or section 45,`
  line
  line `(b) If a tenant who, not having instituted a suit under section 45, has been ejected from his tenancy`
  line `or any part thereof in pursuance of an order under that section denies his liability to be ejected,`
  line
  line `The tenant may, within one year from the date of his dispossession or ejectment, institute a suit for`
  line `recovery of possession or occupancy, or for compensation, or for both.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (71093)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Bar of relief by suit under section 9, Act I of 1877.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71093&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Possession of a tenancy or of any land comprised`
  line `in a tenancy shall not be recoverable under section 9 of the Specific Relief Act, 1877, (I of 1877) by a`
  line `tenant dispossessed thereof`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (71095)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Private transfer of right of occupancy under section 5 by tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71095&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant having a right`
  line `of occupancy under section 5 may transfer that right by sale, gift or mortgage, subject to the conditions`
  line `mentioned in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If he intends to transfer the right by sale, gift, mortgage by conditional sale or usufructuary`
  line `mortgage, he shall cause notice of his intention to be served on his landlord through a Revenue-officer,`
  line `and shall defer proceeding with the transfer for a period of one month from the date on which the notice is`
  line served.
  line
  line `(3) Within that period of one month the landlord may claim to purchase the right at such value as a`
  line `Revenue-officer may, on application made to him in this behalf, fix.`
  line
  line `(4) when the application to the Revenue-officer is to fix the value of a right of occupancy which is`
  line `already mortgaged, he shall fix the value of the right as if it were not mortgaged.`
  line
  line `(5) The landlord shall be deemed to have purchased the right if he pays the value to the`
  line `revenue-officer within such time as that officer appoints.`
  line
  line `(6) On the value being so paid, the right of occupancy shall be extinct, and the Revenue-officer shall,`
  line `on the application of the landlord, put the landlord in possession of the tenancy.`
  line
  line `(7) If the right of occupancy was already mortgaged, the tenancy shall pass to the landlord,`
  line `unencumbered by the mortgage, but the mortgage-debt shall be a charge on the purchase-money.`
  line
  line `(8) If there is no such charge as aforesaid, the Revenue-officer shall, subject to any directions which he`
  line `may receive from any Court, pay the purchase-money to the tenant.`
  line
  line `(9) If there is such a charge, the Revenue-officer shall, subject as aforesaid, either apply in discharge`
  line `of the purchase-money as the mortgage-debt so much of the purchase-money as is required for that`
  line `purpose and pay the balance, if any, to the tenant, or retain the purchase-money pending the decision of a`
  line `Civil Court as to the person or persons entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(10) Where there are several landlords of a tenancy, any one of them pay be deemed to be the landlord`
  line `for the purposes of this section.`
  line
  line `(11) No suit or other preceding shall be instituted against the Secretary of State for India in Council, or`
  line `against any officer of the Government, in respect of anything done by a Revenue-officer under the two`
  line `last foregoing sub-sections, but nothing in this sub-section shall prevent any person entitled to receive the`
  line `whole or any part of the purchase-money from recovering it from a person to whom it has been paid by a`
  line Revenue-officer.
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (71096)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Procedure on foreclosure of mortgage of right of occupancy under section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71096&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `mortgagee of a right of occupancy under section 5 proposes to foreclose his mortgage, or otherwise`
  line `enforce his lien on the land subject to the right, the provisions of the last foregoing section shall, so far as`
  line `they can be made applicable, apply as if the mortgagee were the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (71097)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Sale of right of occupancy under section 5 in execution of decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71097&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) A right of occupancy`
  line `under section 5 may be sold in execution of a decree or order of a Court ;`
  line
  line `(2) But notice of an intended sale of any such right shall be given by the Court to the landlord, and if at`
  line `any time before the close of the day on which the sale takes place the landlord pays to the Court or to the`
  line `officer conducting the sale a deposit of twenty-five per centum on the highest bid made at the sale, he`
  line `shall be declared to be the purchaser instead of the person who made that bid.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (71098)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Transfer of right of occupancy under any other section than section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71098&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `A right of occupancy`
  line `under any other section than section 5 shall not be attached or sold in execution of a decree or order of`
  line `any Court or, without the previous consent in writing of the landlord, be transferred by private contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (71099)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Rights and liabilities of transferee of right of occupancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71099&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `When a right of occupancy has been`
  line `transferred by sale, gift or usufructuary mortgage to a person other than the landlord, that person shall, in`
  line `respect of the land in which the right subsists, have the same rights, and be subject to the same`
  line `liabilities, as the tenant to whom before the transfer the right belonged had and was subject to.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (71100)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Subletting.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71100&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant having a right of occupancy in land may, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act and to the conditions of any written contract between him and his landlord, sublet the land or any`
  line `part thereof for any term not exceeding seven years.`
  line
  line `(2) A person to whom land is sublet by a tenant having a right of occupancy therein shall, in respect of`
  line `that land, and so far as regards the landlord, be, jointly with the tenant, subject to all the liabilities of the`
  line `tenant under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (71101)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Succession to right of occupancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71101&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a tenant having a right of occupancy in any land`
  line `dies, the right shall devolve.—`
  line
  line `(a) on his male lineal descendants, if any, in the male line of`
  line `descent, and,`
  line
  line `(b) failing such descendants, on his widow, if any until she dies or re-marries or abandons the land`
  line `or is under the provisions of this Act ejected therefrom, and,`
  line
  line `(c) failing such descendants and widow, or, if the deceased tenant left a widow, then when her`
  line `interest terminates under clause (b) of this sub-section, on his male collateral relatives in the male line`
  line `of descent from the common ancestor of the deceased tenant and those relatives :`
  line `Provided, with respect to clause (c) of this sub-section, that the common ancestor occupied the`
  line land.
  line
  line `(2) As among descendants and collateral relatives claiming under sub-section (1), the right shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of that sub-section, devolve as if it were land left by the deceased in the village`
  line `in which the land subject to the right is situate.`
  line
  line `(3) When the widow of a deceased tenant succeeds to a right of occupancy, she shall not transfer the`
  line `right by sale, gift or mortgage, or by sub-lease for a term exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `(4) If the deceased tenant has left no such persons as are mentioned in sub-section (1) on whom his`
  line `right of occupancy may devolve under that sub-section, the right shall be extinguished.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (71270)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Enhancement of rent in consideration of an improvement made by a landlord on the tenancy of an occupancy-tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71270&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a landlord has, with the permission mentioned in the last foregoing`
  line `section, made an improvement on the tenancy of a tenant having a right of occupancy, he may apply to`
  line `the Collector fir an enhancement of the rent of the tenant.`
  line
  line `(2) If the tenant is a tenant to whom section 20 applies, the Collector shall enhance his rent to the share`
  line `or rates, or with reference to the rent in gross, as the case may be, paid by tenants, having a similar right`
  line `of occupancy, for land of a similar description and with similar advantages.`
  line
  line `(3) If the tenant is a tenant to whom section 22 applies, the Collector shall enhance his rent to such`
  line `amount as the tenant would be liable to pay under that section if the land-revenue were re-assessed.`
  line
  line `(4) When the improvement ceases to exist, the Collector may, on the application of the tenant, reduce`
  line `the tenant’s rent,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a tenant to whom sub-section (2) applies, to the share or rates, or with reference to`
  line `the rent in gross, as the case may be, paid by tenants, having a similar right of occupancy, for land of a`
  line `similar description and with similar advantages, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a tenant to whom sub-section (3) applies, to such an amount as the tenant would`
  line `be liable to pay if the land revenue were re-assessed.`
  line
  line `(5) Sections 25 and 26 shall be construed as applying to an application under this section, and a suit`
  line `shall not lie in any Court for any purpose for which an application might be made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (71271)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Liability to pay compensation for improvements to tenants on ejectment or on enhancement of his rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71271&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, a tenant who has made an improvement`
  line `on his tenancy in accordance with this Act shall not be ejected, and the rent payable by him shall not be`
  line `enhanced, until he has received compensation for the improvement`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (71112)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Compensation for disturbance of clearing tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71112&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant who has cleared and brought`
  line `under cultivation waste-land in which he has not a right of occupancy shall, if ejected from that land, be`
  line `entitled to receive from the landlord as compensation for disturbance, in addition to any compensation for`
  line `improvements, a sum to be determined by a Revenue Court or Revenue-officer in accordance with the`
  line `merits of the case, but not exceeding five years' rent of the land:`
  line
  line `Provided that a tenant who is a joint owner of land to which this section applies shall not be entitled to`
  line `compensation for disturbance on ejectment from the land or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If rent has been paid for the land by division or appraisement of the produce, or by rates fixed with`
  line `reference to the nature of the crops grown, or if not rent, or no rent other than the land revenue of the land`
  line `and the rates and cesses chargeable thereon, has been paid therefor, the compensation may be computed`
  line `as if double the amount of the land-revenue of the land were the annual rent thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (71113)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Determination of compensation by Revenue Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71113&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every suit by a tenant to contest his`
  line `liability to ejectment or by a landlord to eject a tenant or to enhance his rent, the Court shall direct the`
  line `tenant to file a statement of his claim, if any, to compensation for improvements or for disturbance and of`
  line `the grounds thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court decrees the ejectment of the tenant or the enhancement of his rent, it shall determine`
  line `the amount of compensation, if any, due to the tenant, and shall stay execution of the decree until the`
  line `landlord pays into Court that amount less any arrears of rent or costs proved to the satisfaction f the Court`
  line `to be due to him from the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (71114)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Determination of compensation by Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71114&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `In either of the following cases,`
  line namely—
  line
  line `(a) when a notice has been served on a tenant under section 44,`
  line
  line `(b) when a notice of ejectment has been served on a tenant under section 45 and the tenant has not`
  line `instituted a suit to contest his liability to be ejected, the tenant may apply to the Revenue-officer`
  line `having authority to order his ejectment under section 44 or section 45, as the case may be, to`
  line `determine the amount of compensation due to him for improvements or for disturbance, or for both,`
  line `and the Revenue-officer shall determine the amount, if any, accordingly and stay the ejectment of the`
  line `tenant until the landlord pays to the Revenue-officer the amount so determined less any arrears of rent`
  line `or costs proved to the satisfaction of the Revenue-officer to be due to the landlord from the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (71115)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Matters to be regarded in assessment of compensation for improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71115&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `In estimating the`
  line `compensation to be awarded under this Chapter to a tenant for an improvement, the Court or Revenueofficer shall have regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount by which the value or the produce of the tenancy, or the value of that produce, is`
  line `increased by the improvement;`
  line
  line `(b) the condition of the improvement and the probable`
  line `duration of its effects;`
  line
  line `(c) the labour and capital required for the making of such an improvement;`
  line
  line `(d) any reduction or remission of rent or other advantage allowed to the tenant by the landlord in`
  line `consideration of the improvement; and`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a reclamation, or of the conversion of unirrigated into irrigated land the length of`
  line `time during which the tenant has had the benefit of the improvement.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (71116)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Form of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71116&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) the compensation shall be made by payment in money, unless the`
  line `parties agree that it be made in whole or in part by the grant of a beneficial lease of land or in some other`
  line way.
  line
  line `(2) If the parties so agree, the Court or Revenue-officer shall, make an order accordingly`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (71118)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title Revenue-officers.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71118&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be the same classes of Revenue-officers under this Act as`
  line `under the Punjab Land-revenue Act, 1887 (XVII of 1887) and, in the absence of any order of the Local`
  line `Government to the contrary, a Revenue-officer of any class having jurisdiction within any local limits`
  line `under that Act shall be a Revenue-officer of the same class having jurisdiction within the same local`
  line `limits under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) the expressions “Collector” and “Financial Commissioner” have the same meaning in this Act as in`
  line `the Punjab Land-Revenue Act, 1887`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (71119)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Applications and proceedings cognizable by Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71119&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) the following applications`
  line `and proceedings shall be disposed of by Revenue-officers as such, and no Court shall take cognizance of`
  line `any dispute or matter with respect to which any such application or proceeding might be made or had:-`
  line
  line `FIRST GROUP`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings under section 27 for the adjustment of rents expressed in terms of the land-revenue;`
  line
  line `(b) proceedings relating to the remission and suspension of rent under section 30;`
  line
  line `(c) applications under section 43 for the ejectment of a tenant against whom a decree for an arrear`
  line `of rent in respect of his tenancy has been passed and remains unsatisfied;`
  line
  line `(d) applications under section 45, sub-section (5) for the ejectment of a tenant on whom a notice of`
  line `ejectment has been served and who has not instituted a suit to contest his liability to be ejected but has`
  line `claimed compensation under section 71;`
  line
  line `(e) applications under section 53 or section 54 for the fixing of the value of a right of occupancy;`
  line
  line `(f) applications under section 53 or section 54 by landlords for possession of land, the right of`
  line `occupancy in which has become extinct;`
  line
  line `(g) proceedings under Chapter VI with respect to the award of compensation for improvements or`
  line disturbance;
  line
  line `SECOND GROUP`
  line
  line `(h) application under section 17 with respect to the division or appraisement of produce;`
  line
  line `(i) applications under section 45, sub-section (5), for the ejectment of a tenant on whom a notice of`
  line `ejectment has been served and notice of ejetment has been served and who has not instituted a suit to`
  line `contest his liability to be ejected and has not claimed compensation under section 71;`
  line
  line `(j) applications for the determination.-`
  line
  line `(i) under section 49 of the rent payable for land occupied by crops uncut or ungathered at the`
  line `time of an order being made for the ejectment of a tenant; or`
  line
  line `(ii) under section 49 or section 74 of then value of such crops or of the sum payable to the tenant`
  line `for labour and capital expended by him in preparing land for sowing.`
  line
  line `THIRD GROUP`
  line
  line `(k) applications under section 31 by tenants to deposit rent;`
  line
  line `(l) applications under section 36 for service of notice of relinquishment;`
  line
  line `(m) applications under section 43 for service of notice of ejectment;`
  line
  line `(n) applications under section 53 or section 54 for service of notice of intended transfer or of`
  line `intended foreclosure or other enforcement of lien;`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided by any rule made by the Financial Commissioner in this behalf,-`
  line
  line `(a) a Collector or an Assistant Collector of the first grade may dispose of any of the applications`
  line `and proceedings mentioned in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) an Assistant Collector of the second grade, not being a Naib-Tehsildar, may dispose of any of`
  line `the applications mentioned in the second and third groups of that sub-section; and`
  line
  line `(c) a Naib-Tehsildar, when invested with the powers of an Assistant Collector of the second grade,`
  line `may dispose of any of the applications mentioned in the third group of that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (71120)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Revenue Courts and suits cognizable by them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71120&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Revenue-officer is exercising`
  line `jurisdiction with respect to any such suit as is described in sub-section (3), or with respect to an appeal or`
  line `other proceeding arising out of any such suit, he shall be called a Revenue Court.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be the same classes of Revenue Courts as of Revenue-officers under this Act, and, in`
  line `the absence of any order of the Local Government to the contrary, a Revenue-officer of any class having`
  line `jurisdiction within any local limits under this Act shall be a Revenue Court of the same class having`
  line `jurisdiction within the same local limits.`
  line
  line `(3) The following suits shall be Instituted in and heard and determined by Revenue Courts, and no`
  line `other Court shall take cognizance of any dispute or matter with respect to which any such suit might be`
  line `instituted:-`
  line
  line `FIRST GROUP.`
  line
  line `(a) Suits between landlord and tenant for enhancement or reduction of rent under section 24;`
  line
  line `(b) Suits between landlord and tenant for addition to or abatement of rent under section 28 or for`
  line `commutation of rent;`
  line
  line `(c) Suits under section 34 for the determination of rent or other sum on the expiration of the term of an`
  line `assessment of land-revenue;`
  line
  line `SECOND GROUP.`
  line
  line `(d) suits by a tenant to establish a claim to a right of occupancy, or by a landlord to prove that a tenant`
  line `has not such a right;`
  line
  line `(e) suits by a landlord to eject a tenant;`
  line
  line `(f) suits by a tenant under section 45 to contest liability to ejectment, when notice of ejectment has`
  line `been served ;`
  line
  line `(g) suits by a tenant under section 50 for recovery of possession or occupancy, or for compensation, or`
  line `for both;`
  line
  line `(h) suits by a landlord to set aside a transfer made of a right of occupancy, or to dispossess a person to`
  line `whom such a transfer has been made, or for both purposes;`
  line
  line `(i) any other suit between landlord and tenant arising out of a lease or conditions on which a tenancy is`
  line held;
  line
  line `(j) suits for sums payable on account of village cesses or village-expenses;`
  line
  line `(k) suits by a co-sharer in an estate or holding for a share of the profits thereof or for a settlement of`
  line accounts;
  line
  line `(l) suits for the recovery of over-payments of rent or land-revenue or of any other demand for which a`
  line `suit lies in a Revenue Court under this sub-section:`
  line
  line `(m) Suits relating to the emoluments of kanungos, zaildars, inamdars or village-officers;`
  line
  line `THIRD GROUP.`
  line
  line `(n) Suits by a landlord for arrears of rent or the money-equivalent of rent, or for sums recoverable`
  line `under section 14;`
  line
  line `(o) Suits by a landowner to recover moneys claimed as due for the enjoyment of rights in or over land`
  line `or in water, including rights of irrigation, rights over fisheries, rights of pasturage and forest-rights;`
  line
  line `(p) Suits for sums payable on account of land-revenue or of any other demand recoverable as an arrear`
  line `of land-revenue under any enactment for the time being in force, and by a superior landowner for other`
  line `sums due to him as such.`
  line
  line `(4) Except as otherwise provided by any rule made by the Financial Commissioner in this behalf,-`
  line
  line `(a) a Collector may near and determine any or the suits mentioned in sub-section (3) ;`
  line
  line `(b) an Assistant Collector of the first grade may hear and determine any of the suits mentioned in the`
  line `second and third groups of that sub-section, and, if he has by name been specially empowered in this`
  line `behalf by the Local Government, any of the suits mentioned in the first group; and`
  line
  line `(c) an Assistant Collector of the second grade may hear determine any of the suits mentioned in the`
  line `third group.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (71121)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Superintendence and control of Revenue-officers and Revenue Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71121&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general`
  line `superintendence and control over all other Revenue-officers and Revenue Courts shall be vested in, and`
  line `all such officers and Courts shall be`
  line `subordinate to, the Financial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Financial Commissioner, a`
  line `Commissioner shall control all other Revenue-officers and Revenue`
  line `Courts in his division.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject as aforesaid and to the control of the Commissioner a Collector shall control all other`
  line `Revenue-officers and Revenue Courts in his district.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (71122)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Power to distribute business and withdraw and transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71122&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial`
  line `Commissioner or a Commissioner or Collector may by written order distribute, in such manner as he`
  line thinksfit,
  line `any business cognizable by any Revenue-officer`
  line `or Revenue Court under his control.`
  line
  line `(2) the Financial Commissioner or a Commissioner or Collector may withdraw any case pending`
  line `before any Revenue-officer or Revenue Court under his control, and either dispose of it himself or by`
  line `written order refer it for disposal to any other Revenue-officer or Revenue Court under his control.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not empower any Revenue-officer or`
  line `Revenue Court to exercise any powers or deal with any business which he or it would not be competent to`
  line `exercise or deal with within the local limits of his or its own jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (71123)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71123&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules thereunder, an appeal shall lie from`
  line `an original or appellate order or decree made under this Act by a Revenue-officer or Revenue Court; as`
  line `follows, namely :—`
  line
  line `(a) to the Collector when the order or decree is made by an Assistant Collector of either grade;`
  line
  line `(b) to the Commissioner when the order or decree is made by a`
  line Collector;
  line
  line `(c) to the Financial Commissioner when the order or`
  line `decree is made by a Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that —`
  line
  line `(i) an appeal from an order or decree made by an Assistant Collector of the first grade specially`
  line `empowered by name in that behalf by the Local Government in a suit mentioned in the first group`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 77 shall lie to the Commissioner and not to the Collector;`
  line
  line `(ii) when an original order or decree is confirmed on first appeal, a further appeal shall not lie;`
  line
  line `(iii) when any such order or decree is modified or reversed on appeal by the Collector, the order`
  line `or decree made by the Commissioner on further appeal, if any, to him shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (71124)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Limitation for appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71124&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `the period of limitation for an appeal under the last foregoing section`
  line `shall run from the date of the order or decree appealed against, and shall be as follows, that is to say:—`
  line
  line `(a) when the appeal lies to the Collector—thirty days;`
  line
  line `(b) when the appeal lies to the Commissioner—sixty days;`
  line
  line `(c) when the appeal lies to the Financial`
  line `Commissioner—ninety days;`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (71125)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Review by Revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71125&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer, as such, may either of his own motion or`
  line `on the application of any party interested, review, and on so reviewing modify, reverse or confirm any`
  line `order passed by himself or by any of his predecessors in office :`
  line
  line `Provided as follows: —`
  line
  line `(a) when a Commissioner or Collector thinks it necessary to review any order which he has not`
  line `himself passed and when a Revenue-officer of a class below that of Collector proposes to review any`
  line `order whether passed by himself or by any of his predecessors in officer he shall first obtain the`
  line `sanction of the Revenue-officer to whose control he is immediately subject;`
  line
  line `(b) an application for review of an order shall not be entertained unless it is made within ninety`
  line `days from the passing of the order or unless the applicant satisfies the Revenue-officer that he had`
  line `sufficient cause for not making the application within that period;`
  line
  line `(c) an order shall not be modified or reversed unless reasonable notice has been given to the parties`
  line `affected there by to appear and be heard in support of the order;`
  line
  line `(d) an order against which an appeal has been preferred shall not be reviewed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section the Collector shall be deemed to be the successor in office of any`
  line `Revenue-officer of a lower class who has left the district or has ceased to exercise powers as a`
  line `Revenue-officer and to whom there is no successor in office.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall not lie from an order refusing to review, or confirming on review, a previous order.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (71126)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Computation of periods limited for appeals and applications for review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71126&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `In the computation`
  line `of the period for an appeal from, or an application for the review of, an order under this Act, the limitation`
  line `therefore shall be governed by the Indian Limitation Act, 1877, (XV of 1877).`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (71127)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power to call for, examine and revise proceedings of Revenue officers and Revenue Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71127&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner may at any time call for the record of any case pending before`
  line `or disposed of by, any Revenue-officer or Revenue Courts subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) A Commissioner or Collector may call for the record of any case pending before or disposed of by,`
  line `any Revenue-officer or Revenue Court under his control.`
  line
  line `(3) If in any case in which a Commissioner or Collector has called for a record he is of opinion that the`
  line `proceedings taken or the order or decree made should be modified or reversed he shall submit the record`
  line `with his opinion on the case for the orders of the Financial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) If, after examining a record called for by himself under sub-section (1) or submitted to him under`
  line `sub-section (3), the Financial Commissioner is of opinion that it is inexpedient to interfere with the`
  line `proceedings or the order or decree, he shall pass an order accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) If, after examining the record the Financial Commissioner is of opinion that it is expedient to`
  line `interfere with the proceedings or the order or decree on any ground on which the Chief Court in the`
  line `exercise of its revisional jurisdiction may under the law fir the time being in force interfere with the`
  line `proceedings or an order or decree of a Civil Court, he shall fix a day for hearing the case, and may, on`
  line `that or any subsequent day to which he may adjourn the hearing on which he may appoint in this`
  line `behalf, pass such order as he thinks fit in the case.`
  line
  line `(6) Except when the Financial Commissioner fixes under sub-section (5) a day for hearing the case, no`
  line `party has any right to be heard before the Financial Commissioner when exercising his powers under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (71129)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Procedure of Revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71129&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may make rules consistent with this`
  line `Act for regulating the procedure of Revenue-officers under this Act in cases in which a procedure is not`
  line `prescribed by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The rules may provide, among other matters, for the mode of enforcing orders of ejectment from,`
  line `and delivery of possession of, immoveable property, and rules providing for those matters may confer on`
  line `a Revenue-officer all or any of the powers in regard to contempts, resistance and the like which a Civil`
  line `Court may exercise in the execution of a decree whereby it has adjudged ejectment from, or delivery of`
  line `possession of, such property.`
  line
  line `(3) The rules may also provide for the mode of executing orders as to costs and may adapt to`
  line `proceedings under this Act all or any of the provisions of the Punjab Land-Revenue Act, 1887, (XVII of`
  line `1887) with respect to arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the rules under this section, a Revenue-officer may refer any case which he is`
  line `empowered to dispose of under this Act to another Revenue-officer for investigation and report, and may`
  line `decide the case upon the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (71272)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Persons by whom appearances may be made before Revenue officers as such and not as Revenue Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71272&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Appearances before a Revenue-officer as such, and application to and acts to be`
  line `done before him, under this Act may be made or done.`
  line
  line `(a) by the parties themselves, or`
  line
  line `(b) by their recognized agents or a legal practitioner :`
  line `Provided that the employment of a recognized agent or legal practitioner shall not excuse the personal`
  line `attendance of a party to any proceeding in any case in which personal attendance is specially required by`
  line `an order of the officer.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), recognized agents shall be such persons as the Local`
  line `Government may by notification declare in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The fees of a legal practitioner shall not be allowed as cost in any proceeding before a Revenueofficer under this Act, unless that officer considers, for reasons to be recorded by him in writing, that the`
  line `fees should be allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (71145)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Place of sitting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71145&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Assistant Collector may exercise his powers under this Act at any place`
  line `within the limits of the district in which he is employed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any other Revenue-officer or Revenue court may only exercise his or its powers under this Act`
  line `within the local limits of his or its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (71146)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title Holidays.
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71146&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner, with the approval of the Local Government, shall`
  line `publish in the local Official Gazette before the commencement of each calendar year a list of days to be`
  line `observed in that year as holidays by all or any Revenue-officers`
  line `and Revenue Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) A Proceeding had before a Revenue-officer or Revenue court on a day specified in the list as a day`
  line `to be observed by the officer or Court as a holiday shall not be invalid by reason only of its having been`
  line `had on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (71147)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Discharge of duties of Collector dying or being disabled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71147&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `When a Collector dies or is`
  line `disabled from performing his duties, the officer who succeeds temporarily to the chief executive`
  line `administration of the district under any orders which may be generally or specially issued by the Local`
  line `Government in this behalf shall be deemed to be a Collector under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (71148)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Retention of powers by Revenue officer on transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71148&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `When a Revenue-officer of any class`
  line `who, either as such or as a Revenue Court, has under the foregoing provisions of this Act any powers to`
  line `be exercised in any local area is transferred from that local area to another as a Revenue-officer or`
  line `Revenue Court of the same or a higher, class, he shall continue to exercise those powers in that other local`
  line `area, unless the Local Government otherwise directs or has otherwise directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (71149)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Conferment of powers of Revenue officer or Revenue Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71149&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may`
  line `by notification confer on any person.—`
  line
  line `(a) all or any of the powers of a Financial Commissioner, Commissioner or Collector under this`
  line `Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) all or any of the powers with which an Assistant Collector of either grade is, or may be,`
  line `invested thereunder,`
  line `and may by notification withdraw any powers as conferred.`
  line
  line `(2) A person on whom powers are conferred under sub-section (1) shall exercise those powers within`
  line `such local limits and in such classes of cases as the Local Government may direct, and, except as`
  line `otherwise directed by the Local Government, shall for all purposes connected with the exercise thereof be`
  line `deemed a Financial Commissioner, Commissioner, Collector or Assistant Collector, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Before conferring powers on the Judge of a Civil Court under sub-section (1), the Local`
  line `Government shall consult the Chief Court.`
  line
  line `(4) If any of the powers of a Collector under section 78, section 79, section 80 or section 82 are`
  line `conferred on an Assistant Collector, they shall, unless the Local Government by special order otherwise`
  line `directs, be exercised by him subject to the control of the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (71150)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Power for Financial Commissioner to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71150&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner may, in`
  line `addition to the other rules which may be made by him under this Act, make rules consistent with this Act`
  line `and any other enactment for the time being in force—`
  line
  line `(a) determining, notwithstanding anything in any record-or-rights, the number and amount of the`
  line `instalments and the times by and at which rent is to be paid;`
  line
  line `(b) for the guidance of Revenue-officers in determining, for the purposes of this Act, the amount of`
  line `the land-revenue of any land;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing, for all or any of the territories to which this Act extends the periods during which in`
  line `proceedings held under this Act, a Revenue-officer or Revenue Court is not, except for reasons of`
  line `urgency to be recorded, to issue any process of arrest against, tenant or against a landowner who`
  line `cultivates his own land;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the procedure in cases where persons are entitled to inspect records of Revenueofficer or Revenue Courts, or to obtain copies of the same, and prescribing the fees payable for`
  line `searches and copies ;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing forms for such books, entries, statistics and accounts as the Financial Commissioner`
  line `thinks necessary to be kept, made or compiled in Revenue-officers or Revenue Courts or submitted to`
  line `any authority;`
  line
  line `(f) declaring what shall be the language of any of those offices and Courts, and determining in what`
  line `cases persons practising in those officers and Courts shall be permitted to address the presiding`
  line `officers thereof in English; and`
  line
  line `(g) generally for the guidance of Revenue-officers and other persons in matters connected with the`
  line `enforcement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under clause (a) of sub-section (1), rent shall be payable by the instalments`
  line `and at the times by and at which it is now payable.`
  line
  line `(3) Rules made by the Financial Commissioner under this or any other section of this Act shall not`
  line `take effect until they have been sanctioned by the Local Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (71151)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Rules to be made after previous publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71151&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `The power to make any rules under this Act is`
  line `subject to the control of the Governor General in council, and to the condition of the rules being made`
  line `after precious publication`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (71152)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Powers exercisable by Financial Commissioner from time to time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71152&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `all powers conferred by`
  line `this Act on the Financial Commissioner may be exercised from time to time as occasion requires.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (71153)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Nullity of certain entries in records-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71153&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `An entry in any record-of-rights providing.—`
  line
  line `(a) that a landlord may prevent a tenant from making, or eject him for making, such improvements`
  line `on his tenancy as he is entitled to make under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) that a tenant ejected form his tenancy shall not be entitled to compensation for improvements`
  line `or for disturbance in any case in which he would under this Act be entitled to compensation`
  line `therefor, or`
  line
  line `(c) that a landlord may eject a tenant otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall be void to that extent.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (71154)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Nullity of certain agreements contrary to the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71154&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in any agreement made`
  line `between a landlord and a tenant after the passing of this Act shall.—`
  line
  line `(a) override any of the provisions of this Act with respect to the acquisition of a right of occupancy,`
  line `or the reduction, remission or suspension of rent, or the enhancement of the rent of a tenant having a`
  line `right of occupancy under section 5 or section 6, or`
  line
  line `(b) take away or limit the right of a tenant as determined by this Act to make improvements and`
  line `claim compensation therefor, or, where compensation for disturbance can be claimed under this Act, to`
  line `claim such compensation, or`
  line
  line `(c) entitle a landlord to eject a tenant otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall apply to an agreement by which a tenant binds`
  line `himself to pay an enhanced rent in consideration of an improvement which has been, or is to be, made in`
  line `respect of his tenancy by, or at expense of, his landlord, and to the benefit of which the tenant is not`
  line `otherwise entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (71155)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Saving of other agreements when in writing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71155&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `Save as expressly provided in this Act, nothing`
  line `in this Act shall affect the operation of any agreement between a landlord and a tenant, when the`
  line `agreement either is in writing or has been recorded in a record-of-rights before the passing of the Punjab`
  line `Land-Revenue Act, 1887, (XVII of 1887) or been entered by order of a Revenue-officer in a record-ofrights or annual record under the provisions of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (71156)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Effect of certain entries made in records-of-rights before November, 1871.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328&sectionId=71156&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00006_188716_1667986253328
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `An entry made`
  line `with respect to any of the following matters before the eighteenth day of November, 1871 and attested by`
  line `the proper officer, in the record of a regular settlement sanctioned by the local Government, namely :`
  line
  line `(a) the enhancement or abatement of the rent of a tenant having a right of occupancy, or the`
  line `commutation of rent in kind into rent in money or of rent in money into rent in kind, or the taking of`
  line `rent in kind by division or appraisement`
  line `of the produce or other procedure of a like nature, or`
  line
  line `(b) the letting or under-letting of land in which there is a right of occupancy by the tenant having`
  line `that right, or the alienation of or succession to land in which such a right subsists;`
  line `shall be deemed to be an agreement within the meaning`
  line `of the last foregoing section.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
